### Executive Summary  
AME delivered an exceptionally strong Q1, significantly exceeding EPS guidance with diluted EPS of $1.07, driven by robust operational execution and an impressive 122% free cash flow (FCF) conversion. Despite modest 1% revenue growth, the company achieved a record $2 billion backlog, signaling sustained demand and strong revenue visibility. Management’s credible upward revision of full-year organic sales growth guidance for both segments (EIG and EMG) from mid-single-digits to high-single-digits underscores an accelerated growth trajectory.

